Demonstration of persistent communication in a loop.

Unlike previous example, here we have multiple request, each of which
sending/receiving a portion of a 2D array.

NOTE: As before we can start the operation with a call to *_start functions,
      but this time in a loop. instead of waiting for them one by one with
      MPI_Wait, we call MPI_Waitall once.

        MPI_Waitall(req_count, &req, &status);

      NOTE: when using MPI_Waitall, use MPI_STATUS*ES*_IGNORE, instead of
            MPI_STATUS_IGNORE

NOTE: when passing array of buffers and requests, make sure to pass the right
      pointer to send and receive initialization functions.

          buffers[][]
          requests[]

          MPI_Send_init(&buffers[i], ..., &requests[i])
          MPI_Request_free(requests)

